WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:09.140 --> 00:00:12.820
Crochet folded coin purse

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:27.640
What do you need?

00:00:28.680 --> 00:00:33.260
Yarn (recommended for 4.5 knitting needles)

00:00:35.200 --> 00:00:38.940
Crochet hook size US G (4 mm)

00:00:41.220 --> 00:00:44.940
Scissors

00:00:47.380 --> 00:00:50.960
Yarn neddle

00:00:53.080 --> 00:00:57.000
1 button

00:00:59.720 --> 00:01:02.560
Let's begin...

00:01:04.780 --> 00:01:09.380
Begin with the purse bottom (base)

00:01:09.880 --> 00:01:13.100
Make a slip knot

00:01:14.400 --> 00:01:20.480
Foundation chain: chain 5

00:01:25.220 --> 00:01:40.940
Row 1: chain 1, 5 single crochet (work in the back loops of each chain)

00:01:46.300 --> 00:01:51.600
Continue turning your work,

00:01:52.660 --> 00:01:59.860
Work 1 single crochet more in the last chain (increase),

00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:06.640
Turn and work 5 single crochet (1 in each chain)

00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:14.520
The 1st single crochet goes in the same chain you worked the last 2

00:02:16.080 --> 00:02:24.700
Continue working the single crochet stitches

00:02:28.040 --> 00:02:34.760
Work 1 single crochet more in the last chain

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:38.320
After row 1 you'll have 12 stitches

00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:43.180
Don't finish this row with a slip stitch... we're going to work in spiral way

00:02:45.740 --> 00:02:48.760
Row 2: repeat from * to * all around

00:02:49.220 --> 00:02:53.460
(Mark the 1st stitch with a stitch marker)

00:02:54.380 --> 00:03:13.160
*1 single crochet, 1 increase (2 single crochet in 1 chain)*

00:03:16.040 --> 00:03:20.100
After row 2 you'll have 18 stitches

00:03:20.720 --> 00:03:25.020
Row 3: repeat from * to *

00:03:26.100 --> 00:03:55.920
*2 single crochet, 1 increase*

00:03:59.360 --> 00:04:03.480
After Row 3 you'll have 24 stiches

00:04:05.180 --> 00:04:10.800
Row 4: repeat: *3 single crochet, 1 increase*

00:04:11.120 --> 00:04:13.560
After row 4 you'll have 30 stitches

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:21.920
Row 5: repeat: *14 single crochet, 1 increase*

00:04:22.100 --> 00:04:25.180
After row 5 you'll have 32 stitches

00:04:25.780 --> 00:04:31.800
Rows 6 to 22: 32 single crochet

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:49.760
Row 23: chain 3 (as 1st double crochet),

00:04:50.360 --> 00:05:00.040
chain 3,

00:05:01.200 --> 00:05:05.980
1 double crochet in the same chain (1st one)

00:05:10.320 --> 00:05:21.960
skip 3 chains, 1 double crochet

00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:27.600
chain 3,

00:05:29.140 --> 00:05:34.740
1 double crochet in the same chain you worked the last double crochet

00:05:35.540 --> 00:05:40.020
Repeat *1 double crochet, chain 3, 1 double crochet in the same chain, skip 3*

00:05:41.980 --> 00:05:55.260
To finish row 23: slip stitch to the 3rd chain

00:05:56.760 --> 00:06:01.660
Now we have to work the edge...

00:06:02.700 --> 00:06:16.200
Edge row 1: chain 1, and repeat: *3 single crochet in the 3 chain arch,

00:06:16.980 --> 00:06:25.800
1 single crochet at the junction between the groups of 2 double crochet and 3 chains

00:06:28.220 --> 00:06:32.800
Rows 2 and 3: 32 single crochet

00:06:34.720 --> 00:06:54.360
To finish row 3 work 1 slip stitch

00:06:55.540 --> 00:07:05.720
cut and weave the tail through the stitches of the fabric to hide it.

00:07:08.240 --> 00:07:15.180
To finish the coin purse sew the button

00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:26.420
First calculate where to sew the button

00:07:28.140 --> 00:07:40.840
Fold the purse and mark where you'll sew the button

00:07:43.780 --> 00:07:47.740
Sew the button

00:07:48.540 --> 00:07:51.700
And that's it...!

